  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study is an observational, multicenter, prospective cohort study aimed at evaluating a
      5-year screening programme for chronic kidney disease(CKD) in a population of elderly
      patients, aged 65 years or more, in China.To analyze the etiology and composition spectrum,
      the incidence of complications and co-morbidities.To assess the correlation between daily
      living ability, mental and physical function, quality of life, nutritional status and
      prognosis.To develop biomarkers of renal aging.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
